
[1]enthusiastical

   ENTHUSIAS'TICAL, a. Filled with enthusiasm, or the conceit of special
   intercourse with God or revelations from him.

   1. Highly excited; warm and ardent; zealous in pursuit of an object;
   heated to animation. Our author was an enthusiastic lover of poetry and
   admirer of Homer.

   2. Elevated; warm; tinctured with enthusiasm. The speaker addressed the
   audience in enthusiastic strains.
